# Git commits

Use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/):

```
<type>[optional scope]: <description>

[optional body]
```

**Types:** `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`, `ci`, `chore`, `perf`

**Scopes (examples):** `api`, `web`, `core`, `db`, `billing`, `runtime`, `mcp`, `smoke`

**Rules:**

- One logical change per commit; do not commit unless the user asked.
- Never commit `.env`, keys, or `.artifacts`.
- After platform changes, mention smoke status in the PR body, not only in chat.
- Breaking SDK contract changes: `feat(sdk)!:` or footer `BREAKING CHANGE:`.
